Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,[ED]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[Eyecatch]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Conan Episode 1014 "The \NNovelist Known as the Demon King"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[OP]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.84,0:00:25.48,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Crap, it's 3:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.48,0:00:27.92,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I need to get home soon, or \NI'll miss out on my snack.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.05,0:00:29.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Your snack? Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.54,0:00:31.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.91,0:00:37.18,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I believe the author Tawake \NShintaro's mansion is around there.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.48,0:00:39.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the mystery writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.99,0:00:42.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Every book he publishes is a success.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.25,0:00:44.03,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's no wonder he's got such a nice place.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.29,0:00:46.42,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.79,0:00:50.60,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You again?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.60,0:00:52.74,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If Division One is here, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.07,0:00:53.89,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.89,0:00:59.49,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The author Tawake Shintaro was found \Nshot to death inside this residence.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.90,0:01:01.99,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What? Shot to death?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.48,0:01:07.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A journey of a thousand miles \Nstarts with the first step!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.08,0:01:09.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Solve 1,000 mysteries and enter a new world!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.65,0:01:11.86,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Shots are fired at a popular author!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.86,0:01:13.93,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The shady room is its own mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.93,0:01:15.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.51,0:01:17.23,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.23,0:01:19.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.03,0:03:07.04,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(401,1)}The Novelist Known as the Demon King
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.61,0:03:04.22,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Novelist Known as the Demon King!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.37,0:03:10.92,Tawake,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(400,439)}Tawake Shintaro (55)\NMystery Writer
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.52,0:03:11.04,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The victim is Tawake \NShintaro-san, 55 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.04,0:03:14.79,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,As you know, he was a mystery writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.14,0:03:18.51,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The cause of death was blood loss \Nfrom a gunshot wound to the abdomen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.76,0:03:23.41,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We believe the weapon was this shotgun \Nfound on the floor near the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.96,0:03:25.18,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.04,0:03:30.02,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The victim was shot while \Nsleeping on the sofa.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.99,0:03:37.15,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The windows of this study face north, so the \Nlights were kept on even during the daytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.45,0:03:41.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,A room doesn't get sunlight \Nwith north-facing windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.25,0:03:46.28,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,According to forensics, the estimated \Ntime of death is around noon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.29,0:03:51.75,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He was shot with that shotgun, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.93,0:03:55.25,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely, since it was \Nleft on the floor there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.50,0:03:57.88,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Let's review the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.32,0:04:03.21,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,While Tawake was sleeping on the \Nsofa, the culprit entered the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.21,0:04:07.97,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,killed him with a shotgun, dropped the \Nmurder weapon, and fled the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.44,0:04:10.01,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.91,0:04:14.96,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely. Since the glass door in \Nthe living room was partially open,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.96,0:04:17.61,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,we believe the culprit entered \Nand exited through there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.68,0:04:20.61,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Take the body away for an autopsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.54,0:04:27.24,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We found no signs that the culprit searched \Nthe room, so we don't believe they were a thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.94,0:04:29.40,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Could the motive have been hatred?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.56,0:04:35.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.21,0:04:37.55,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's a bloodstain.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.55,0:04:39.95,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,This must've splattered \Nhere when he was shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.95,0:04:45.13,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But since there's no blood on the curtains, \Nthat means they were open then, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.76,0:04:48.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did the culprit take the time to close them?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.40,0:04:54.73,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the case, then \Nwhy did they do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.20,0:04:58.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They were probably trying to \Ndelay the discovery of the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.37,0:05:00.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It would give them more time to get away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.95,0:05:04.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But who'd be looking in through this window?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.11,0:05:04.90,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.33,0:05:07.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it visible from the next house over?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.95,0:05:10.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What's up with that house?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.84,0:05:15.00,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The weather's so nice, but \Nall the shutters are closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.64,0:05:21.27,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently the neighbors moved away \Nlast week. It's currently unoccupied.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.27,0:05:22.63,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's empty, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.15,0:05:23.94,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.75,0:05:27.09,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,There's blood on this as well,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.62,0:05:30.60,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,but there isn't a drop on \Nthe floor or wall around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.12,0:05:35.73,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Was that stand located \Nelsewhere during the murder
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.73,0:05:38.48,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,and moved afterwards by the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.93,0:05:40.98,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why would that be necessary?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.56,0:05:45.61,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure, I'm back from \Nquestioning the neighbors.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.13,0:05:49.25,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody saw any suspicious persons.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.25,0:05:51.05,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Also, in the neighborhood...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.40,0:05:55.11,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,There wasn't anyone who heard a gunshot.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.46,0:05:59.96,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not surprised no one heard \Nanything with this racket.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.73,0:06:04.13,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The body was discovered by \NTawake's apprentices, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.13,0:06:06.05,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We're having them wait in the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.52,0:06:09.91,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Tawake Shintaro had apprentices, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.34,0:06:13.31,Akaike,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(447,1)}Akaike Naoya (38)\NTawake's Apprentice
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.62,0:06:15.60,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}These four are Tawake-san's apprentices.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.35,0:06:16.31,Degawa,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(440,1)}Degawa Miyuki (30)\NTawake's Apprentice
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.35,0:06:19.31,Bito,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(443,1)}Bito Ryunosuke (35)\NTawake's Apprentice
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.40,0:06:22.31,Chigasaki,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(396,1)}Chigasaki Haruo (33)\NTawake's Apprentice
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.76,0:06:25.61,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,These two found the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.61,0:06:27.39,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Akaike Naoya.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.39,0:06:28.95,DCMain,MIYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Degawa Miyuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.46,0:06:32.79,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,These two are apprentices as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.79,0:06:35.08,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,They came as quickly as they could \Nonce we reached out to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.49,0:06:37.42,DCMain,BITO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Bito Ryunosuke.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.42,0:06:39.08,DCMain,CHIGASAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Chigasaki Haruo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.48,0:06:43.84,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,We took turns on a daily rotation \Nperforming odd jobs for Tawake-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.27,0:06:49.22,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,It was my turn today, so I'd been \Nat the mansion since this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.68,0:06:52.56,DCItalic,TAWAKE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(187,1)}You can leave for now, Akaike.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.56,0:06:54.46,DCItalic,TAWAKE,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I'd like \Nyou to do for me later.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.46,0:06:56.22,DCItalic,TAWAKE,0000,0000,0000,,Come back around three.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.78,0:06:59.59,DCItalic,TAWAKE,0000,0000,0000,,I've got something to tell you \Nthen, so bring Miyuki with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.59,0:07:02.03,DCItalic,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir. See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.92,0:07:06.06,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,When the two of us returned...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.97,0:07:15.60,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,We rushed to call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.60,0:07:18.70,DCMain,MIYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, we haven't \Ntouched the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.33,0:07:22.21,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then it was the culprit who \Ntouched the curtains and stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.34,0:07:27.21,DCMain,MIYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Akaike-san, we \Nshould probably call them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.21,0:07:28.59,7PM,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(255,129)}7 PM
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.21,0:07:28.59,7PM,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(303,264)\frz357.7}Shiga Dentist
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.57,0:07:28.59,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.84,0:07:32.16,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't call them soon, \Nit'll cause trouble later.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.76,0:07:34.34,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.59,0:07:38.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Who would it cause trouble for?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.83,0:07:40.10,DCMain,MIYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,The dentist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.43,0:07:44.35,DCMain,MIYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Akaike-san was told to make \Nan appointment yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.98,0:07:47.27,DCItalic,TAWAKE,0000,0000,0000,,Damn molars.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.27,0:07:49.09,DCItalic,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.87,0:07:52.03,DCItalic,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,I was able to make an appointment \Nfor tomorrow night at seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.55,0:07:55.48,DCMain,MIYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,But now that he's dead...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.48,0:07:59.52,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to cancel the \Nappointment I made yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.52,0:08:00.25,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.58,0:08:03.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Tawake-san had bad teeth, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.29,0:08:09.13,DCMain,BITO,0000,0000,0000,,The Demon King won't have to \Nworry about cavities anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.44,0:08:10.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Demon King?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.57,0:08:14.26,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you call him the Demon King?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.41,0:08:21.19,DCMain,BITO,0000,0000,0000,,They'll find out as they \Ncontinue their investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.06,0:08:28.07,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,Officer, to tell you the truth, Tawake-sensei\Nwas considered a brilliant hitmaker,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.43,0:08:32.47,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,but there's no way he could've written \Nmore than ten books each year.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.47,0:08:38.83,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,The books he published over the past \Nfew years were actually written by us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.09,0:08:40.33,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.09,0:08:47.08,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,He'd make us write them and \Nthen make a few changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.41,0:08:49.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He barely wrote anything himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.22,0:08:53.47,DCMain,BITO,0000,0000,0000,,It was an open secret in the industry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.65,0:08:56.56,DCMain,MIYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,We were paid for our work,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.56,0:08:59.85,DCMain,MIYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,but we didn't want to be ghostwriters.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.85,0:09:01.97,DCMain,MIYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,But we couldn't defy him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.51,0:09:06.64,DCItalic,TAWAKE,0000,0000,0000,,If you keep working for me, I'll help \Nyou debut when the time is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.64,0:09:10.97,DCItalic,TAWAKE,0000,0000,0000,,But if you run away from me, \NI'll make sure you never debut!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.19,0:09:17.11,DCMain,MIYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, his books are popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.11,0:09:20.47,DCMain,MIYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,His influence in the publishing \Nindustry was absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.31,0:09:24.85,DCMain,CHIGASAKI,0000,0000,0000,,But he lied about helping us debut.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.85,0:09:27.48,DCMain,CHIGASAKI,0000,0000,0000,,We jumped at the opportunity to \Napprentice with an author we admired,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.48,0:09:28.79,DCMain,CHIGASAKI,0000,0000,0000,,but this place was like a labor camp.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.10,0:09:30.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why you called him the Demon King.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.64,0:09:34.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,All four of you had problems with Tawake-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.11,0:09:39.55,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The only way you could become \Nindependent was if he went away.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.02,0:09:40.76,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.03,0:09:44.14,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, you resented him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.49,0:09:46.77,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You had motives for murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.09,0:09:50.77,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying one of us killed him?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.65,0:09:53.65,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure, the \Nforensics team is leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.43,0:09:56.68,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We'll stay here a little longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.68,0:09:58.67,DCMain,BITO,0000,0000,0000,,He was shot using that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.67,0:10:00.20,DCMain,CHIGASAKI,0000,0000,0000,,That gun...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.58,0:10:11.54,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,It's not inside the locker.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.02,0:10:15.30,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it. That gun \Nbelonged to Tawake-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.48,0:10:18.06,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The weapon belonged to the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.50,0:10:26.06,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,He secretly stored his unlicensed gun here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.25,0:10:28.56,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,And you all knew about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.06,0:10:31.51,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you, we're innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.51,0:10:35.42,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,We know suspicion would \Nfall on us if we used it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.42,0:10:37.82,DCMain,MIYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way we'd do something so foolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.52,0:10:39.75,DCMain,BITO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.25,0:10:43.43,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps that's exactly why you used it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.43,0:10:47.12,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If you were the culprit, there's \Nno way you'd use that gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.12,0:10:49.62,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You planned to use that excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.33,0:10:53.13,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,Once you start thinking that \Nway, there's no end to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.57,0:10:57.63,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But won't suspicion be cleared \Nonce your alibis are verified?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.96,0:10:59.26,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.45,0:11:03.01,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Then could you tell us where you were
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.30,0:11:06.06,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,and what you were doing around noon?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.06,0:11:20.40,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We were able to confirm Akaike-san's alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.40,0:11:23.18,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We found several people to verify it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.96,0:11:28.48,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,However, we were unable to \Nconfirm Degawa-san, Bito-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.48,0:11:30.25,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,and Chigasaki-san's alibis.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.54,0:11:34.00,DCMain,MIYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Of course you couldn't. We were writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.00,0:11:34.99,DCMain,BITO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.99,0:11:35.75,DCMain,CHIGASAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.02,0:11:38.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,For now, we've narrowed down \Nfour suspects to three.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.10,0:11:40.92,DCMain,MIYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute! You mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.16,0:11:45.96,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, we're not assuming \None of you is the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.96,0:11:48.93,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But without clear alibis...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.22,0:11:53.89,DCMain,BITO,0000,0000,0000,,Chigasaki, it's because of your stupid \Nactions that the police suspect me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.89,0:11:57.44,DCMain,CHIGASAKI,0000,0000,0000,,What? But it's Miyuki who seems \Nlike she could've done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.27,0:12:01.45,DCMain,MIYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Bito-san is a hundred times \Nmore suspicious than I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.65,0:12:04.67,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,Cut it out, guys. Don't \Npoint fingers at each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.86,0:12:09.09,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I know forced infighting when I see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.09,0:12:12.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Did the three of you scheme \Nto kill Tawake together?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.62,0:12:13.67,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.33,0:12:17.05,DCMain,CHIGASAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Why is this happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.64,0:12:20.07,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,Don't cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.07,0:12:23.77,DCMain,CHIGASAKI,0000,0000,0000,,You're able to say that \Nbecause you have an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.77,0:12:27.34,DCMain,BITO,0000,0000,0000,,You're responsible for this, Akaike-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.34,0:12:32.03,DCMain,BITO,0000,0000,0000,,You did nothing about the Demon King's \Ntyranny even though you're the oldest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.03,0:12:32.93,DCMain,MIYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.93,0:12:33.98,DCMain,CHIGASAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.84,0:12:38.09,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.09,0:12:42.42,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The autopsy found sleeping \Npills in the body's system.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.42,0:12:43.74,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Sleeping pills?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.29,0:12:48.49,DCMain,BITO,0000,0000,0000,,The Demon King never took sleeping pills.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.85,0:12:51.91,DCMain,MIYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit probably \Nsecretly fed them to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.91,0:12:54.34,DCMain,MIYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,but why was it necessary to put him to sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.34,0:12:58.12,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, if it was possible \Nto feed him sleeping pills,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.12,0:13:00.88,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,then they should've been \Nable to poison him, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.25,0:13:02.26,DCMain,CHIGASAKI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.26,0:13:04.17,DCMain,CHIGASAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Poisoning him would've been easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.73,0:13:06.72,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,But they shot him instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.72,0:13:09.60,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,There must be some reason \Nthe culprit did that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.81,0:13:10.96,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.96,0:13:13.27,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose all four of \Nthem are mystery writers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.27,0:13:16.10,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They're practically mystery-solving experts.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.52,0:13:17.93,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.93,0:13:24.97,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,By using that gun, the culprit was trying to \Nmake it look like one of us was the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.97,0:13:26.41,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,That must be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.41,0:13:28.55,DCMain,BITO,0000,0000,0000,,We've been set up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.49,0:13:32.59,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But something's not right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.42,0:13:34.56,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.90,0:13:37.76,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This curtain was opened and closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.33,0:13:39.56,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.58,0:13:41.91,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the case, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.78,0:13:44.36,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It must've left some trace behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.55,0:13:53.52,Tawake Sign,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(195,1)}Tawake
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.52,0:14:18.73,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A piece of aluminum foil.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.73,0:14:20.50,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They made it using this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.21,0:14:28.99,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But how do I prove it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.99,0:14:31.17,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Judging by the culprit's personality...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.66,0:14:34.51,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is it possible that that was...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.51,0:14:37.58,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fs26\bord3\shad0\fnTimes New Roman\c&HB0A491&\3c&H738C57&\move(95,35,185,16)}Shiga Dentist
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.91,0:14:41.58,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.58,0:14:43.62,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That just leaves the weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.62,0:14:46.14,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's supposed to be clear \Nall day tomorrow, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.14,0:14:47.53,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That'll work.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.53,0:14:53.75,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit must be one of the apprentices.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.75,0:14:57.43,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Which one of the three \Nwithout an alibi is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.93,0:15:02.75,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, he said he figured \Nout who the culprit is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.12,0:15:04.36,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.36,0:15:07.63,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently the culprit will show \Nup at the crime scene tomorrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.97,0:15:10.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,around noon, the same \Ntime the murder happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.96,0:15:14.14,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What? The inspector said \Nto leave for the day?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.32,0:15:14.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.91,0:15:17.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He asked us to come back tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.03,0:15:18.13,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.10,0:15:21.90,The Next Day,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(445,1)\blur2\3c&H17181C&\pos(321,265)}The Next Day
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.92,0:15:32.05,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-kun, what did you mean when \Nyou said the culprit would show up?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.05,0:15:32.66,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.99,0:15:37.65,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean everyone \Ncurrently present is innocent?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.65,0:15:39.04,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Great!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.38,0:15:41.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector, I came like you told me to—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.12,0:15:47.43,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I came like you told me to come, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.43,0:15:49.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.88,0:15:52.32,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Sleeping Kogoro!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.32,0:15:57.57,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, we were distracted by the whodunnit
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.57,0:16:03.61,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,of who killed Tawake and \Noverlooked something important:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.61,0:16:04.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The howdunnit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.98,0:16:08.61,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,How did the culprit kill Tawake?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.86,0:16:10.04,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.04,0:16:12.98,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,They put him to sleep using sleeping pills,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.98,0:16:16.37,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,entered the room, and shot him to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.57,0:16:19.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,First, Detective Takagi, remember \Nwhat I told you this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.82,0:16:22.37,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir. Chiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.77,0:16:23.61,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.46,0:16:28.29,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,That looks about right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.29,0:16:29.75,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Detective Chiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.49,0:16:35.13,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Next, the gun has been tied to the stand \Nthat was by the entrance of this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.13,0:16:38.01,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's currently beside the \Nchair I'm sitting in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.16,0:16:43.27,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The gun has been loaded with a \Npaint bullet instead of a live round.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.67,0:16:46.79,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We've set up everything according \Nto your instructions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.79,0:16:48.50,DCMain,MIYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Could this be?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.50,0:16:50.90,DCMain,CHIGASAKI,0000,0000,0000,,It certainly seems that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.90,0:16:53.44,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,It's not possible in this study.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.44,0:16:55.61,DCMain,BITO,0000,0000,0000,,After all, the windows face north.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.74,0:16:57.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mister, I'm opening the curtains.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.49,0:16:59.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.74,0:17:01.58,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.34,0:17:08.67,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,A mirror?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.77,0:17:11.42,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's a concave mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.42,0:17:15.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,A handmade one made by wrapping a \Nwooden frame with aluminum foil.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.28,0:17:20.10,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I asked Professor Agasa to make it for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.64,0:17:25.48,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit who shot Tawake \Nshould appear soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.91,0:17:32.98,DCMain,BITO,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.98,0:17:34.11,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,It really is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.37,0:17:35.49,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.98,0:17:47.54,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The focused sunlight ignited the shell.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.78,0:17:51.80,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. This phenomenon \Noccasionally causes fires.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.09,0:17:55.81,DCMain,MIYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,This trick has been used \Nrepeatedly in mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.81,0:17:59.36,DCMain,CHIGASAKI,0000,0000,0000,,But this trick is normally made \Npossibly by south-facing rooms...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.36,0:18:03.71,DCMain,BITO,0000,0000,0000,,Was pulled off in this north-facing \Nstudy using a mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.71,0:18:04.56,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.56,0:18:07.94,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit used this method to kill Tawake.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.39,0:18:12.77,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Since the culprit didn't want anyone to \Nnotice the gunshot and look into the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.77,0:18:16.44,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,they waited for this time of day \Nwhen the sound would be drowned out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.17,0:18:19.63,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,They used the construction noises.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.63,0:18:22.13,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,That explains the sleeping pills, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.13,0:18:27.21,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,They couldn't hit the victim if he \Nmoved, so they had to put him to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.97,0:18:30.21,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In order to conceal this method,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.51,0:18:34.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,after committing the murder, the culprit \Nmoved the stand used to fix the gun in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.55,0:18:39.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In order to allow the focused \Nsunlight into the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.25,0:18:41.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,they had to leave the curtains open.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.89,0:18:45.31,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,To keep their trick from being discovered,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.31,0:18:47.09,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,the culprit closed them \Nafter committing the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.24,0:18:51.48,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Any of the apprentices could \Nhave used this method.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.98,0:18:55.43,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Since it's such a famous trick, \Nthey all knew about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.98,0:19:00.24,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,However, the reason they \Nused this method was because
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.24,0:19:04.39,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,by fabricating an alibi for Tawake's death,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.39,0:19:06.49,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,they wouldn't be considered a suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.16,0:19:11.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the person \Nwith an alibi is the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.63,0:19:13.50,DCMain,CHIGASAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.50,0:19:14.80,DCMain,BITO,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.80,0:19:16.25,DCMain,MIYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,It was Akaike-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.93,0:19:19.26,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,But Mori-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.52,0:19:21.97,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It was your turn yesterday \Nto perform odd jobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.97,0:19:24.70,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You secretly fed Tawake sleeping pills.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.27,0:19:27.20,DCItalic,TAWAKE,0000,0000,0000,,I feel so tired for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.72,0:19:30.29,DCItalic,TAWAKE,0000,0000,0000,,You can leave for the day, Akaike.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.88,0:19:33.09,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You took the gun out of the locker,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.09,0:19:36.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,attached it to the stand, \Nopened the curtains,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.85,0:19:38.75,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,opened the shutters of the house next door,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.75,0:19:43.14,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,set up the concave mirror, \Nfabricated an alibi around noon,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.84,0:19:45.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and killed Tawake.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.74,0:19:51.36,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then you returned to the crime \Nscene to clean up your trick
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.36,0:19:53.84,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and left the glass door in \Nthe living room slightly open
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.84,0:19:56.04,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,so it would seem like the \Nculprit entered through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.68,0:20:04.19,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You destroyed the concave mirror made \Nof aluminum foil in the house next door
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.65,0:20:05.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and closed the shutters.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.83,0:20:08.83,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You had Degawa Miyuki-san accompany you
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.83,0:20:11.38,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and discovered the body first
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.38,0:20:16.31,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,so she could testify that you \Ndidn't touch the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.17,0:20:21.26,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,This is all speculation, Mori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.26,0:20:25.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I borrowed the key from the real estate \Noffice so I could examine the house next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.46,0:20:28.29,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently you did, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.80,0:20:31.10,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You claimed that Tawake was \Nthinking about buying it
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.10,0:20:36.18,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and wanted to take a look around \Ninside and made a spare key.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.18,0:20:38.17,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,That's speculation as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.62,0:20:42.42,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But you gave yourself away, Akaike-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.85,0:20:44.43,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm talking about the dentist appointment.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.18,0:20:50.36,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I confirmed with them that no \Nappointment was ever made for Tawake.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.97,0:20:53.31,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,When you made the appointment \Nthe other day...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.33,0:20:56.62,DCItalic,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,I was able to make an appointment \Nfor tomorrow night at seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.62,0:21:00.57,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,...you were just pretending, like you \Ndid when you called to cancel yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.74,0:21:04.57,DCItalic,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to cancel the appointment \NI made yesterday. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.76,0:21:06.24,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You pretended to call.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.86,0:21:11.08,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's because you knew there was \Nno point in making an appointment.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.33,0:21:12.42,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.42,0:21:16.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You knew beforehand that Tawake would die.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.17,0:21:19.92,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You knew something only \Nthe culprit would know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.55,0:21:28.75,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,Tawake-sensei had missed plenty \Nof appointments until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.75,0:21:31.55,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,If I made an appointment \NI knew would be canceled,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.55,0:21:34.81,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,I would've caused trouble for them again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.39,0:21:38.79,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I decided to take down
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.79,0:21:43.22,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,the Demon King who caused nothing \Nbut problems for others myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.22,0:21:48.54,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to free the four of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.54,0:21:50.44,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,I had to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.44,0:21:52.40,DCMain,AKAIKE,0000,0000,0000,,After all, I'm the oldest.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.01,0:23:24.20,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm disgusted by Tawake Shintaro, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.20,0:23:26.56,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe he was making \Nhis apprentices write his books.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.56,0:23:31.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He's like a detective who takes credit \Nfor someone else's mystery-solving.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.94,0:23:33.81,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,There's no detective like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.12,0:23:37.52,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, what's happening? I feel \Na stinging pain in my chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.52,0:23:39.06,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is he actually experiencing some guilt?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.59,0:23:41.74,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It was a toothpick!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.74,0:23:43.76,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,672)}He doesn't feel guilty at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.02,0:24:09.05,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.41,0:23:48.28,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.50,0:23:51.37,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,We spotted Detective Chiba, \Nso we decided to follow him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.37,0:23:52.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're on a stakeout, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.66,0:23:54.03,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,We'll help.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.24,0:23:58.54,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,How did you know the culprit lives \Nin the apartment across the street?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.74,0:24:00.54,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Takagi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.73,0:24:02.67,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,They're all getting ready to go out.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.67,0:24:04.63,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps they're making a deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.49,0:24:08.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What are they doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.05,0:24:15.05,DCNextEp,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Stakeout
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.55,0:24:12.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is "Stakeout!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.07,0:24:32.27,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.07,0:24:34.99,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Ball, Frisbee, and Stuffed Animal
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.27,0:24:34.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A ball, a Frisbee, and a stuffed animal!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.99,0:24:36.35,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I've got my beer, kaki-pi \Ncrisps, and walnuts!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.99,0:24:39.99,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.35,0:24:38.08,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm ready for a stakeout!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.08,0:24:39.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You mean ready to get drunk.
